- Lot of 4 framed pieces of art
- Includes artists such as Patti Harris Googe and Angela Gamble
- One piece signed/numbered Patti Harris Googe, numbered 1216/5000
- One numbered print by Patti Harris Googe, numbered 2898/5000
- Collaborative artwork by various artists entitled &#34;Wet Canvas Round Robin&#34;
- Frame material: brown wood / faux wood
- Sizes range from largest 27&#34; x 35&#34; to smallest 10&#34; x 12&#34;
- Condition: good with minor wear to frames; glass/matte damaged or dirty
- Bring packing materials and moving help. 
Pickup category timeslot {A}

- Category: Wooden carvings/statues, wall art/frames, decorative box, sculptures
- Material: Wood
- Style/Origin: African / tribal
- Free standing pieces sized 29&#34; and 22&#34;
- Artwork sized 17&#34;14&#34; to 7&#34;x9&#34;
- Condition: Good - minor wear
- Included items: Multiple carved figures, framed pictures/frames, woven fan/basket, carved decorative box
- Bring packing materials and moving assistance as needed. 
Pickup category timeslot {B}

description:
Navajo First Phase Silver and Turquoise Concha Belt 
fourth quarter 19th century

seven oval-shaped silver conchas with scalloped edges decorated with stamping and diamond-shaped cutouts, accented with intertwined stamped design; rectangular buckle, set with two turquoise cabochons and accented with repoussé; not marked

belt length 45 inches;
concha length 4-3/8 inches x width 3-1/2 inches;
buckle length 3-1/4 inches x width 3 inches;
weight 607.2 dwt.


The Collection of Michelle Smith, Washington, D.C.

